      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(memory): support global baselines and agent overrides",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nMemory has one canonical configuration model:\n\n- `memory` is the global baseline.\n- `agents.list[].memory` is the per-agent override.\n- Resolution deep-merges objects. Only source collections are additive and deduped: `memory.qmd.paths`, `memory.search.extraPaths`, and `memory.search.qmd.extraCollections`. Other arrays replace the baseline value.\n- Configuration inheritance does not make runtime state shared. SQLite indexes, agent workspaces, QMD homes, dreaming artifacts, and Memory Wiki state remain agent-local unless a shared path is explicitly configured.\n\n## Before\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"memory\": {\n        \"backend\": \"builtin\",\n        \"search\": { \"provider\": \"openai\" }\n      }\n    },\n    \"list\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"research\",\n        \"memorySearch\": { \"extraPaths\": [\"~/research-notes\"] },\n        \"dreaming\": { \"enabled\": true }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## After\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"memory\": {\n    \"backend\": \"builtin\",\n    \"search\": {\n      \"provider\": \"openai\",\n      \"extraPaths\": [\"~/team-notes\"]\n    },\n    \"extensions\": {\n      \"memory-core\": { \"dreaming\": { \"enabled\": true } }\n    }\n  },\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"list\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"research\",\n        \"memory\": {\n          \"backend\": \"qmd\",\n          \"search\": { \"extraPaths\": [\"~/research-notes\"] },\n          \"extensions\": {\n            \"memory-core\": { \"dreaming\": { \"enabled\": false } }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Migration And Doctor\n\nUse `openclaw doctor --lint` to find legacy config and `openclaw doctor --fix` to rewrite it.\n\n- `agents.defaults.memory` moves to the root `memory` baseline. Existing root settings win; doctor deep-fills missing fields from the former default.\n- `memorySearch` and `agents.defaults.memorySearch` move to `memory.search`.\n- `agents.list[].memorySearch` moves to `agents.list[].memory.search`.\n- `agents.list[].dreaming` moves to `agents.list[].memory.extensions.memory-core.dreaming`.\n- Legacy Memory Wiki config moves to `memory.extensions.memory-wiki` or the matching agent override.\n- `memorySearch.store.path` is removed. Built-in indexes now live in each agent database.\n- Legacy `provider: \"auto\"` becomes explicit `\"openai\"`.\n\n## Operational Changes\n\n- Dreaming schedules only agents with dreaming enabled. Disabling dreaming for every configured agent remains a full opt-out; default-agent fallback is only used when no valid agents are configured.\n- Gateway, UI, QA, policy, secret collection, startup provider detection, QMD, and Memory Wiki all resolve the same global-baseline plus agent-override model.\n- Startup warnings now point at the real configuration path: `memory.search.*` for baseline settings and `agents.*.memory.search.*` for agent-only overrides.\n- Private dreaming artifacts stay excluded from builtin and QMD indexing, including cross-workspace and symlink-alias paths.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Focused Vitest suites passed across config/doctor migration, memory-host SDK, Memory Core dreaming and QMD, policy, secrets, gateway startup, Dreams UI, QA config, and QA scenario catalog.\n- `pnpm check:changed` was attempted in Blacksmith Testbox. The runner's full-sync checkout could not complete because it expected source files absent from this older branch source (`apps/android/version.json` and `ui/config/control-ui-chunking.ts`); focused checks above remain green.\n- Final autoreview: no accepted or actionable findings.\n",
